{"pageProps":{"post":{"title":"Next.js is the future","excerpt":"Next.js is an open-source development framework built on top of Node.js enabling React based web applications functionalities such as server-side rendering and generating static websites.","featuredImage":{"url":"https://media.graphcms.com/z1pqUW16Qy6ttPs6heRC"},"author":{"name":"ESC","bio":"ESC helps content creators achieve their dreams.","photo":{"url":"https://media.graphcms.com/UNPhCSU2ScW5CI3Qrq8q"}},"createdAt":"2021-11-12T12:01:17.646885+00:00","slug":"nextjs","content":{"raw":{"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Next.js is a "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/React_(web_framework)","type":"link","title":"React (web framework)","children":[{"text":"React"}],"className":"mw-redirect","openInNewTab":false},{"text":" framework that enables several extra features, including "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Server-side_scripting","type":"link","title":"Server-side scripting","children":[{"text":"server-side rendering"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" and generating "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Static_web_page","type":"link","title":"Static web page","children":[{"text":"static websites"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":"."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-compareStatic-6","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[6]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" React is a "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript_library","type":"link","title":"JavaScript library","children":[{"text":"JavaScript library"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" that is traditionally used to build web applications rendered in the client's browser with JavaScript."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-thakkar1-7","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[7]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" Developers recognize several problems with this strategy however, such as not catering to users who do not have access to JavaScript or have disabled it, potential security issues, significantly extended page loading times, and it can harm the site's overall "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Search_engine_optimization","type":"link","title":"Search engine optimization","children":[{"text":"search engine optimization"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":"."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-thakkar1-7","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[7]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" Frameworks such as Next.js sidestep these problems by allowing some or all of the website to be rendered on the server-side before being sent to the client."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-thakkar1-7","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[7]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":""},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-thakkar2-8","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[8]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" Next.js is one of the most popular components available in React."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-9","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[9]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" It is one of several recommended \"toolchains\" available when starting a new app, all of which provide a layer of abstraction to aid in common tasks."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-SmashingStyle-10","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[10]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" Next.js requires "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Node.js","type":"link","title":"Node.js","children":[{"text":"Node.js"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" and can be initialized using "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Node_Package_Manager","type":"link","title":"Node Package Manager","children":[{"text":"Node Package Manager"}],"className":"mw-redirect","openInNewTab":false},{"text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Google has donated to the Next.js project, contributing 43 pull requests in 2019 where they helped in pruning unused JavaScript, reducing overhead time, and adding improved metrics."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-insiders-11","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[11]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" As of March 2020, the framework is used by many large websites, including "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netflix","type":"link","title":"Netflix","children":[{"text":"Netflix"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":", "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GitHub","type":"link","title":"GitHub","children":[{"text":"GitHub"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":", "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uber","type":"link","title":"Uber","children":[{"text":"Uber"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":", "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ticketmaster","type":"link","title":"Ticketmaster","children":[{"text":"Ticketmaster"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":", and "},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Starbucks","type":"link","title":"Starbucks","children":[{"text":"Starbucks"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":"."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-thakkar1-7","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[7]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" In early 2020, it was announced that Vercel had secured twenty-one million dollars in Series A funding to support improvements to the software."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-simplify-1","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[1]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":" The framework's original author, Guillermo Rauch, is currently the CEO of Vercel and the project's lead developer is Tim Neutkens."},{"href":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Next.js#cite_note-12","type":"link","children":[{"text":"[12]"}],"openInNewTab":false},{"text":""}]}]}},"categories":[{"name":"Web Development","slug":"webdev"},{"name":"React","slug":"react"}]}},"__N_SSG":true}